<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">All four paths end with a first draft of the Recommendations section (3-5 items, specific + evidence-anchored + actionable). No "raise awareness" recommendations.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I can define and distinguish mitigation and adaptation with one Chennai example each, identify which lever applies to my challenge, and draft 3-5 specific, actionable, evidence-anchored Recommendations.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Draft Recommendations (default)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">3-5 recommendations for the GCC audience. Each must be: specific (not "raise awareness"), actionable (something GCC can do with their authority), evidence-anchored (cite YOUR sources). Mark each as adaptation, mitigation, or both.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Recommendations + cost/equity annotation (stretch)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Same as Path A, plus for each recommendation: rough cost estimate (high/medium/low), who benefits, who bears the burden. Equity-aware recommendations score higher on T/T 7-8 — the rubric specifically calls out "address cost, feasibility, and equity."</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Policy Aide on weak recommendations (choice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Draft Recommendations first, then paste them into the <a href="/ai-partners/policy-aide/">Policy Aide</a>. It will push back on any "raise awareness" or "study the problem" recommendations. Rewrite based on its feedback. Document the exchange.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Choice</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">D</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Adaptation-vs-mitigation peer-help (practice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If the distinction is still fuzzy after the bell ringer + Watch, come to the peer-help table. Use the GCC priorities Read handout. Pair with a student who's solid. Mr. Ignash floats.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Pairs · Practice</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

